title: Search underway for man and three children missing from Queensland - 9news.com.au
text:
Search underway for man and three children missing from Queensland By 9NEWS Scott Willmott and Annabella, Memphis and Noah are believed to be headed for Melbourne. (Supplied/NSW Police) 
Police are searching for a man and three children after they disappeared from Queensland over the weekend. 
Scott Willmott is believed to be travelling in New South Wales headed for Melbourne with eight-year-old Annabella, five-year-old Memphis and two-year-old Noah. 
The group was last seen at 11pm on Saturday in a red Ford Laser with Queensland registration plates 737 EMO. 
Police said there were reports the car was seen in Bega yesterday. 
Attempts to contact Mr Willmott have been unsuccessful, police said, and Queensland and NSW officers are calling for anyone with information to call Triple Zero. Â© Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
